Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.01,0:00:07.81,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-sama and Natsuki Subaru-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.81,0:00:11.61,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I would gladly host you two at \Nmy home for as long as you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.04,0:00:13.67,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate that,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.67,0:00:17.69,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,but we do want to get the \Nvillagers back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.69,0:00:19.60,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come back after we take them all home
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.60,0:00:22.50,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and talk to her sponsor, Roswaal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.99,0:00:24.29,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.29,0:00:28.29,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,When you do, I hope I can finally \Nrepay my great debt to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.44,0:00:32.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that big a deal. \NYou helped us out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.29,0:00:35.59,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We even got a reward. Right, Patrasche?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:38.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.16,0:00:39.35,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:41.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Those scales hurt more than I expected!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.88,0:00:44.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know how a daikon radish \Nfeels when it's being grated!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:50.20,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kyun, I've secured Rem-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:51.95,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to keep her still!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.26,0:00:53.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.94,0:00:58.59,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need your rest when you \Nget back to the mansion, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.59,0:00:59.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:03.37,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,You've been working your gate overtime \Nsince you were going up against Sloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:06.92,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,I did clean up all the toxins in your gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.92,0:01:09.04,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,but you need to let it rest for two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.30,0:01:10.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Two months, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.17,0:01:14.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, surely all this crazy stuff \Ncan't keep happening for {\i1}that{\i0} long...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.20,0:01:16.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, did I just set a flag?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.27,0:01:20.83,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,All right, it's time for you to get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:22.24,Default,Felis,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, Crusch-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.24,0:01:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give them a few parting words.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:28.64,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-sama, I wish you good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.07,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to seeing you again very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.58,0:01:39.82,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Crusch-san. Please be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.48,0:01:43.68,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, I won't just be the \None who always needs saving.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.68,0:01:46.37,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'll become someone who can help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.92,0:01:50.60,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,Natsuki Subaru-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.60,0:01:53.67,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you all the best in the future, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.98,Default,Crusch,0000,0000,0000,,I know we will meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.20,0:02:25.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Right, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.46,0:02:31.89,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Subaru, you always sit beside \Nme as if it's the obvious choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.89,0:02:33.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is there something weird about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:37.42,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,No. I felt a little uncomfortable at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.93,0:02:40.89,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,but now it feels strange if \Nyou don't, so it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.12,0:02:45.33,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My painstaking efforts have \Nfinally been rewarded!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.33,0:02:46.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.58,0:02:48.23,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You're teasing me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.41,0:02:51.86,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're still worried about Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:54.98,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for you to hide that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.62,0:02:59.05,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,She's important to you, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.05,0:03:00.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She is! Super important!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:02.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,As important to me as you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.88,0:03:05.08,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You're being very selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.53,0:03:06.91,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:08.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:11.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I feel like such scum,\N I wish I could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.53,0:03:13.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But it's the absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.54,0:03:15.84,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.64,0:03:20.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just say my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.48,0:03:23.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.23,0:03:24.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, have you been there all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.99,0:03:27.32,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I've been here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.32,0:03:30.68,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think I decided \Nto work with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.95,0:03:32.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.30,0:03:35.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You want to negotiate with Roswaal in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.30,0:03:36.46,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't forgotten that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.46,0:03:40.40,Default,otto,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you! My whole \Nlife is riding on this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:42.44,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.44,0:03:45.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Time to say goodbye to you for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.20,0:03:45.78,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, wai—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:57.46,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll find a way to get her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:00.17,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-tan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.40,0:04:04.59,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I think you and I\N are the same in the sense
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.00,0:04:07.89,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,that we act for our own selfish reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:13.27,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that I'm participating in the \Nroyal selection for selfish reasons, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.84,0:04:14.85,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Selfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.47,0:04:18.98,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I can't explain it very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:22.40,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hide anything from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:24.57,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm not sure how to put it into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:32.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We can talk everything out \Nafter we join up with Roswaal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.60,0:04:37.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,He might know something about \Nwhat happened to Rem, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.77,0:04:39.44,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.32,0:04:45.06,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,You two, we'll be reaching \Nour destination soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:51.14,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,No one's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.29,0:04:55.03,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No one around here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.03,0:04:57.50,Default,Kids,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.85,0:05:00.76,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,So Ram and the others haven't \Nreturned from the Sanctuary?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:02.24,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.72,0:05:06.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Emilia-tan, do you \Nknow where the Sanctuary is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:09.28,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I thought {\i1}you{\i0} knew where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:09.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:14.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm late in asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:16.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but what kind of place is \Nthe Sanctuary, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.97,0:05:18.49,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.49,0:05:22.67,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Roswaal only said it was like \Na secret base... and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:23.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.52,0:05:26.13,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.57,0:05:29.14,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I should have asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.32,0:05:31.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! Even if we were in \Na hurry to get to safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.95,0:05:34.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who was way too careless!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:40.95,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have to head to the mansion for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.95,0:05:42.61,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we'll find some clues there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.22,0:05:44.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Otto, come with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:47.24,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,What? To the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:49.85,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so scared after \Nwe've come this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:52.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Take the carriage and the ground \Ndragons around back, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:54.50,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:01.46,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're back, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.17,0:06:03.44,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:04.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.73,0:06:08.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I don't remember \Nlocking the door when we left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:09.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You think we got robbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.04,0:06:13.85,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Beatrice stayed here, so I \Ndon't think we need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.85,0:06:16.68,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she'll come get the \Ndoor for us if we knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:20.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She might come flying through \Nit, looking for Puck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.96,0:06:21.69,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:24.61,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Puck? Puck?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.94,0:06:27.60,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He's not responding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:29.32,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.32,0:06:30.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,How about in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.52,0:06:36.57,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, one moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.59,0:06:41.55,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:44.50,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I have awaited your return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.17,0:06:46.21,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Frederica?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.54,0:06:51.36,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is I, Frederi—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.36,0:06:52.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Those teeth are scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.48,0:06:55.75,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.75,0:06:59.81,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I am Frederica Baumann. I was \Nemployed here in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.29,0:07:02.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.62,0:07:05.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was told there was another maid \Nwho quit just before I came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.18,0:07:10.01,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I merely took my leave for personal reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:14.91,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Then I returned at Ram's request, \Nand found the mansion empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.76,0:07:18.52,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately, a letter I found \Nin the master's office
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.52,0:07:20.71,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,gave me an idea as to what had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.71,0:07:21.60,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.04,0:07:24.17,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And why did Ram ask you to come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:26.49,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,When I returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the kitchen and the trees in the \Ngarden were in a desolate state.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.56,0:07:31.01,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,It was quite awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.33,0:07:34.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty serious reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:38.27,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.27,0:07:42.75,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Ram has always worked hard \Nfor us while you were away,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.75,0:07:44.69,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,so why, in just the past few days...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.67,0:07:50.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,With Rem gone, Ram couldn't \Nhandle the mansion herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:53.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,so she asked Frederica to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.37,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind explaining \Nto me who this girl
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:07:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who bears a striking resemblance to Ram is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.45,0:08:02.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She's Ram's younger sister, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.53,0:08:04.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She's a really nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.93,0:08:08.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,She's kind, strong, and a super-hard worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.57,0:08:12.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Even I could tell that she \Nand Ram were really close.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.58,0:08:16.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you were a good friend to her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:21.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You... probably don't remember, though, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:23.91,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.91,0:08:28.07,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how the master and Ram \Nwill react when they return...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.53,0:08:30.66,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even guess what Roswaal will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.31,0:08:34.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And... I don't want to \Nimagine how Ram will react.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.60,0:08:39.63,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Frederica, have you \Nheard anything from Roswaal?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.63,0:08:44.79,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Sadly, I have no way of knowing all \Nthat goes on in the master's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.43,0:08:51.26,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I believe there are only two people in \Nthis world he trusts enough for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:52.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Two?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:56.68,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Ram and the great spirit of this \Nmansion's forbidden library.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:58.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Great spirit of the forbidden library?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.30,0:09:02.11,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I refer to Beatrice-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:15.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Beako! Long time no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:20.46,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see why the mansion \Nsuddenly seemed so noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.54,0:09:25.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's been worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:27.79,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You should apologize, even if \Nit has to wait until later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.01,0:09:30.67,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:34.17,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I fail to comprehend why I \Nmust apologize, and to whom, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:37.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I could go apologize for you, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:40.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell them you were thanking me with \Ntears and snot streaming down your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.93,0:09:42.81,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make up stories!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.81,0:09:45.60,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't shed tears in a \Nvery long time, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.60,0:09:48.25,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It never hurts to have a good \Nwail every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:50.32,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Those words carry deep meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,coming from a man who bawled in \Nthe lap of the woman he loves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.78,0:09:56.55,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Would you just forget about that already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.55,0:09:58.80,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please get to the point, I suppose?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.80,0:09:59.95,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You weakling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.28,0:10:01.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.67,0:10:07.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,How well do you know what \NRoswaal's thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:13.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Someone told me that you \Nknow how Roswaal thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:15.52,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Who said—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.52,0:10:16.27,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:19.59,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been the \Nhalf-beast girl who just came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.24,0:10:24.28,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,There is a bit of accuracy to \Nwhat she told you, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.28,0:10:28.73,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,But my connection with Roswaal has nothing \Nto do with the current circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.16,0:10:31.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But you stayed here at the mansion by yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:34.07,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,even with no countermeasures in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.34,0:10:36.99,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I'm capable of protecting myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.99,0:10:39.16,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I stayed, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:41.60,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Roswaal has nothing to do with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.60,0:10:46.08,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,That said, I don't believe he had \Nnothing on his mind at all, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.27,0:10:47.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.49,0:10:53.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Were you and I and everyone else \Njust giving him too much credit,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.30,0:10:56.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,thinking he wouldn't go up against \Nthe Witch's Cult with no plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:10:58.46,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:00.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:04.76,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,A Gospel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:08.60,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you, of all people, \Nhave one of those?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.11,0:11:11.22,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I took it off the enemy after a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:14.98,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It belonged to the guy in charge of the witch \Ncultists who surrounded the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.72,0:11:17.69,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,And what became of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:19.11,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:21.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.00,0:11:26.93,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Then you've left me behind, too, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.07,0:11:29.16,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Geuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:31.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.36,0:11:33.85,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,None of your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.35,0:11:38.80,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if you killed Sloth, a Sin Archbishop,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:40.63,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,what happened to his Witch Factor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:43.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Witch... Factor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.75,0:11:46.51,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know what it is? You really don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.02,0:11:51.16,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, then why \Ndid you bother to kill Sloth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.16,0:11:53.15,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,And what is Roswaal...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.15,0:11:56.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, remember? \NRoswaal is at the Sanctuary!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.93,0:11:59.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who wants to \Nknow what he's thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:06.12,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,All the answers you seek lie \Nin the Sanctuary, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.69,0:12:07.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:10.93,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Roswaal's intentions, the meaning of the Gospel,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.93,0:12:14.12,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,answers about the Witch Factor...\NThey're all there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.97,0:12:16.67,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,If you want them, go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:20.76,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,The half-beast girl can \Nlead you there, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:23.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on a second! What's up with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:25.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you suddenly willing to talk to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:27.48,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Also, why do I have to go to \Nthe Sanctuary when you—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:29.07,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I will not tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.64,0:12:32.77,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I have the right to refuse to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.51,0:12:37.04,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I showed you the path that \Nleads to your answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.04,0:12:39.56,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,Do not expect me to indulge \Nyou any further, I suppose!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.56,0:12:41.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Beako... Beatrice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:45.20,Default,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,I am not a tool here for your convenience!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:54.12,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wh-Why did you fly into me just \Nas I was leaving the bathroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:12:57.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you look like you \Nwere about to cry again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.21,0:12:59.09,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Could you please get off of—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.60,0:13:05.13,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,So you really are allowed to enter \NBeatrice-sama's forbidden library?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.36,0:13:07.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What? You thought I wouldn't be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:12.81,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but Emilia-sama has told me \Nwhat a reliable person you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:15.51,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,and she was quite thorough \Nin explaining why,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.99,0:13:18.56,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,so half of me had high\Nhopes that you would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:18.98,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.28,0:13:20.72,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Frederica!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.72,0:13:22.48,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What? What did you tell her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.71,0:13:27.74,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that! I did tell her \Nabout you, but she's exaggerating!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.06,0:13:30.68,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,No, I heard what you said, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.68,0:13:33.37,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,It made me think there must be more \Nto Natsuki-san than meets the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:34.90,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Not you, too, Otto-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.90,0:13:38.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Why wasn't I around to hear all this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:40.42,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I could never say it in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.14,0:13:43.87,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Frederica, back to what you were saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.87,0:13:46.09,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:50.83,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Let us talk it over so you don't \Nfind yourself at a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.83,0:13:52.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Dead end? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:54.88,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you were able to see Beatrice,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:13:58.03,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,whether or not she'd answer your \Nquestion was another matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:14:01.73,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and Beatrice can be \Nvery stubborn, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.20,0:14:05.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That description is way too cute,\N but you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.96,0:14:06.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.21,0:14:10.46,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot I want to talk \Nto Roswaal about, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:12.70,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,So I asked Frederica
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.13,0:14:15.01,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,to tell me where the Sanctuary is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:19.54,Default - flashback,Beatrice,0000,0000,0000,,The half-beast girl can \Nlead you there, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.33,0:14:23.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to tell us \Nwhere it is, Frederica?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:25.77,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I was no match for \NEmilia-sama's persistence,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.77,0:14:29.62,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,even though I have been told not to \Ndisclose any more than necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:33.22,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,But I would like to ask \Nfor a bit of time to prepare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:35.39,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we say two days?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.68,0:14:36.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.28,0:14:41.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right. We'd all be \Nleaving the mansion, so that's—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:44.28,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,No, I will be staying in the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:45.44,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot accompany you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.96,0:14:47.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're not going with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:49.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,How are we supposed to get there, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.93,0:14:54.39,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,You're rather slow on the uptake, Natsuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:15:00.53,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So Otto's gonna get us to the Sanctuary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Because he thinks cooperating \Nwith Emilia in any way possible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.43,0:15:07.71,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,will give Roswaal, her backer, \Na better impression of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.53,0:15:07.05,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No, er...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:09.51,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Otto-kun, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.96,0:15:12.84,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-sama's pure, innocent \Neyes are killing me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.84,0:15:14.80,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! That's exactly right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:18.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The way you wear your ulterior motive on your\N sleeve makes you all the more likable, Otto.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.67,0:15:21.48,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,That's not exactly comforting, \Ncoming from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.77,0:15:23.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.66,0:15:27.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,On that note, you can tell the \Nthree of us about the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.76,0:15:29.19,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:32.43,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,What I am about to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.43,0:15:36.28,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,is the undisclosed location of the Sanctuary \Nof Clemaldy, and how to enter it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.99,0:15:42.08,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,And there is one name you must \Nnot forget as you travel there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:45.50,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Beware of one by the name of "Garfiel."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.02,0:15:47.25,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,At the Sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:53.42,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,he will be the one with whom you \Nmust exercise the most care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.20,0:16:00.98,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.67,0:16:02.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:06.92,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I told Frederica to take good care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.92,0:16:08.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Be good and wait here for me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:20.12,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,You're ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.12,0:16:21.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Sure am, new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.45,0:16:23.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I see you're rocking the uniform already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.76,0:16:24.94,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.07,0:16:29.94,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say goodbye to Rem-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.94,0:16:31.82,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.16,0:16:34.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We're not planning to stay out there long,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.51,0:16:35.89,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but I wanted to see her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.84,0:16:41.47,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take care of Rem for \Nme while I'm gone, Petra?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.13,0:16:44.31,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Understood, Subaru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:48.11,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Still, we started advertising to \Nhire a new maid two days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.11,0:16:50.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and this is your first day \Nactually being in the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.43,0:16:52.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you found the \Nplace without getting lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.37,0:16:57.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And I really admire your decision to \Nleave your parents at such a young age.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:00.63,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,I'm twelve years old! I'm old \Nenough to be a working grown-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.63,0:17:02.29,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:06.24,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,You need to treat me like \Nan adult, too, Subaru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:09.77,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Get better at speaking politely and \Nget Frederica to fully initiate you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.77,0:17:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:11.64,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,'Kay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:12.88,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:21.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot what a pain she can be \Nwhen she's serious about hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.46,0:17:24.89,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Is there really a mysterious room here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.24,0:17:27.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Beatrice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:30.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You know her, right? \NTake care of her for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:35.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You might randomly encounter her \Nwhen opening a door somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.72,0:17:38.87,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Subaru-sama! Aren't you \Nasking a bit much of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.35,0:17:40.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.30,0:17:43.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the only one I can ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.32,0:17:44.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I really am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.01,0:17:49.44,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:52.09,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist, I'll just have to help you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:54.01,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. You're really a huge help.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.43,0:17:57.56,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of the mansion for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.56,0:18:00.22,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,And Rem, Petra, and Beatrice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:02.36,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,You can rely on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:05.18,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Take care during your travels, Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.99,0:18:07.55,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,And take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.26,0:18:10.72,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,This will allow you to get past \Nthe barrier in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.72,0:18:12.94,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,and enter the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.52,0:18:17.78,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,From there, the ground dragons should \Ntake you to the location I described.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:22.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So this stone is the requirement \Nto get through the barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.84,0:18:27.79,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,You have the location and the qualification.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:31.11,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Now you only need the \Nresolve and a strong will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.68,0:18:33.83,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Frederica...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.44,0:18:39.82,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:42.68,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,And do not forget what I said earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:45.87,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. We'll watch out for Garfiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.24,0:18:47.11,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.98,0:18:49.88,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Subaru-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:53.32,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Would you please accept this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.32,0:18:54.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:57.14,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Lending a white handkerchief to a traveler,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:19:00.28,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,who later returns it stained \Nand worn from the journey,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.88,0:19:03.87,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,is an old custom performed as \Na prayer for safe travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:06.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's one of those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.84,0:19:09.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, got it. Thanks, Petra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.49,0:19:10.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I promise I'll return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.83,0:19:20.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What? What brought that reaction on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.98,0:19:23.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,This sudden rebellious phase is making me sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:27.76,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you should hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:32.85,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,The Lost Forest of Clemaldy grows \Nmore dangerous as night approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:38.26,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you a safe journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.39,0:19:41.49,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.17,0:19:45.77,Default,Petra,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better protect the lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.08,0:19:50.09,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,I have done exactly as Master directed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.38,0:19:56.63,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Now everything depends on how \NEmilia-sama overcomes the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.11,0:19:59.12,Default,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing we can do but pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.81,0:20:03.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Puck isn't showing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.28,0:20:05.35,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:07.04,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I've called out to him several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I can feel the link \Nfrom our contract, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.98,0:20:12.18,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Has anything like this happened before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.18,0:20:15.76,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Not very often, but there \Nhave been a few times
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.76,0:20:18.15,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,when he didn't show up for a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.40,0:20:23.53,Default - flashback,Puck,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you to take care of Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.13,0:20:25.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.14,0:20:29.56,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,But I do have contracts \Nwith lesser spirits, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:31.69,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,and I can also fight with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.69,0:20:34.41,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, I'll protect you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.41,0:20:36.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're so manly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.36,0:20:37.36,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.87,0:20:43.34,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Frederica did warn us that \Nsomething might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:45.94,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Garfiel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.94,0:20:50.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Roswaal did mention a few times \Nthat he was going to see him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:51.72,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.01,0:20:53.62,Default,Otto,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:20:59.65,Default - flashback,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Lost Woods of Clemaldy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:03.66,Default - flashback,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,A special barrier there protects the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.08,0:21:07.41,Default - flashback,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,It makes outsiders lose their way, \Nto prevent them from getting close.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:11.12,Default - flashback,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,That is why they call it the "Lost Woods."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.77,0:21:14.19,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So the Sanctuary is just ahead...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:23.78,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia-tan, are you actually nervous?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.78,0:21:25.93,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? How could you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:28.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I know everything about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:32.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's what I'd like \Nto say, but anyone could tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.55,0:21:37.94,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:41.26,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for worrying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:43.49,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,When I think that we're about \Nto arrive at the Sanctuary,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:45.90,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,a village where only demihumans live...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.68,0:21:50.33,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, I should apologize. I wasn't \Nthinking that far ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:54.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there might be more \Nhalf-elves like you there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:59.39,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen any half-elves \Nother than myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.99,0:22:02.63,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,But just maybe, in the Sanctuary...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:05.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'll—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.74,0:22:08.97,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:10.97,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.13,0:22:13.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly have a really bad feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.32,0:22:14.43,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm borrowing this, Emilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.81,0:22:19.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Emilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.72,0:22:33.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Where... am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:44.15,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.44,0:22:46.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Those ears...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.69,0:22:48.13,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an elf?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.30,0:22:51.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait! Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.96,0:23:05.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Is anyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.59,0:23:09.09,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the Sanctuary, \Nsomebody answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.20,0:23:14.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:30.34,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.20,0:23:33.88,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,So that is the root of your desire?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.88,0:23:36.17,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,How very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.88,0:23:48.60,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, did I startle you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.23,0:23:55.43,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,It has been quite a while \Nsince I spoke with anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:23:57.69,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,so perhaps I was too eager.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.96,0:24:01.08,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Echidna...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:06.31,Default,Echidna,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps you would know me \Nbetter as the Witch of Greed?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.96,0:24:09.96,Episode Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\t(1,3010,\fs30)\c&H000000&\bord0}The {\c&HCCCCCC&}Next {\c&H000000&}Location
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.96,0:24:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.41,0:25:18.91,sign_36406_423_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's to save you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.45,0:25:20.95,sign_36406_423_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,to save you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.74,0:25:22.16,sign_36406_423_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.16,0:25:23.66,sign_36406_423_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,how many times
